st/reference-manual/native-image/metadata/) from this repository.\n./README.md:21:For a broader overview of supported libraries and frameworks, you can visit [this page](https://www.graalvm.org/native-image/libraries-and-frameworks/). It lists libraries and frameworks that are tested and ready for GraalVM Native Image.  \n./README.md:49:Built with love by the community and the [GraalVM](https://www.graalvm.org/), [Spring](https://spring.io/projects/spring-boot), and [Micronaut](https://micronaut.io/) teams.\n./forge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:41:        \"ERROR: Unable to locate a GraalVM Java home with native-image. \"\n./forge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:42:        \"Please set GRAALVM_HOME or JAVA_HOME to a GraalVM distribution where bin/native-image exists.\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:48:    \"\"\"Return True when the provided GraalVM home contains native-image.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:54:    \"\"\"Require a GraalVM home environment variable that contains native-image.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:61:            f\"ERROR: Environment variable '{env_var_name}' must point to a GraalVM distribution \"\n./forge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:70:    \"\"\"Return an environment configured to run Gradle with the provided GraalVM.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:78:    \"\"\"Run the library test task with a specific GraalVM/JAVA_HOME.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/workflow_setup.py:98:    \"\"\"Run tests with a specific GraalVM and iterate metadata fixes until they pass.\"\"\"\n./forge/utility_scripts/native_test_verification.py:78:class NativeTestVerificationResult:\n./forge/utility_scripts/native_image_artifact.py:23:class NativeImageEligibility:\n./forge/utility_scripts/native_image_artifact.py:51:        reason = \"Artifact discovery identified this as not applicable to GraalVM Native Image metadata.\"\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:5:This is the best way to provide support for GraalVM Native Image as it makes an out-of-the-box experience for users (no additional work required) and allows you to continuously test and maintain the metadata as part of your project.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:59:* GraalVM Reachability Metadata in this repo only contains JSON files as described\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:99:* `metadata-version`: Specifies the subdirectory where the GraalVM configuration files (e.g., `reflect-config.json`) reside.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:114:* `override`: Boolean. If `true`, excludes outdated builtin GraalVM metadata.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:247:If your library or framework is tested with GraalVM Native Image, consider adding it to [this list](https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/blob/master/metadata/library-and-framework-list.json).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:3:This document describes what the **GraalVM Reachability Metadata Repository** does for its users, who those users are, and the functional requirements that the repository, its build infrastructure, and its automation (Metadata Forge) must meet.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:11:The repository hosts curated, versioned **GraalVM reachability metadata** for community JVM libraries and frameworks, plus the test harness, CI, and AI automation that keep the metadata correct and up to date.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:13:Reachability metadata describes reflection, JNI, resource access, serialization, and proxy use that GraalVM `native-image` cannot determine through static analysis. By centralizing this metadata, the repository allows libraries that are not yet self-contained for native compilation to \"just work\" with `native-image` when consumed via the GraalVM Gradle and Maven plugins.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:19:| **Application developer** using GraalVM Native Image | Build a native image of an application that depends on third-party libraries without writing reachability metadata by hand; check whether a given library is supported; request support for a missing library. | Consumes metadata indirectly — the GraalVM Gradle/Maven plugin downloads it from this repository at build time. Checks support via `curl … check-library-support.sh \\| bash -s \"<group>:<artifact>:<version>\"` or by browsing [the libraries-and-frameworks page](https://www.graalvm.org/native-image/libraries-and-frameworks/). Requests a new library by filing a [`01_support_new_library`](../.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/01_support_new_library.yml) issue, or updates an existing one via [`02_update_existing_library`](../.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/02_update_existing_library.yml). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:43:- A directory tree under `metadata/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/` containing JSON files in the format described by GraalVM's [Native Image Manual Configuration](https://www.graalvm.org/latest/reference-manual/native-image/dynamic-features/Reflection/#manual-configuration) reference.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:54:- Compilation, JVM-mode tests (`javaTest`), and native-image tests (`nativeTest`).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:69:Every two weeks the `create-scheduled-release` workflow packages metadata if it has changed. The packaged artifact is what the GraalVM Gradle/Maven plugins consume.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:103:| `fails-java-run` | Issue | New-version compatibility failed during the `javaTest` / JVM runtime stage. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:165:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:201:- **FR-M-1** Metadata files contain only JSON entries described by GraalVM's manual-configuration reference. Native-image properties (`native-image.properties`) and other build-time tweaks are forbidden — by default every library is runtime-initialized.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:215:- **FR-T-5** Tests must compile under JDK 25 and pass both `javaTest` and `nativeTest` lanes on every JDK/OS combination listed in `ci.json`.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:236:- **FR-CI-5** `verify-new-library-version-compatibility` caps each scheduled run at a fixed library budget and at most 30 newer versions per library, expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, and creates one aggregated GitHub issue per failed `(library, version)` pair.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:242:- **FR-NI-2** `future-defaults-all` is run only against early-access / `latest` / `dev` GraalVM builds, both locally (via `GVM_TCK_NATIVE_IMAGE_MODE=future-defaults-all`) and in scheduled CI lanes that explicitly opt in via `ci.json`'s `nativeImageModeJavaVersions`.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:272:- Bi-weekly release artifacts consumed by the GraalVM Gradle/Maven plugins.\n./forge/utility_scripts/native_metadata_exploration.py:53:class NativeExplorationFailure:\n./forge/utility_scripts/native_metadata_exploration.py:63:class NativeExplorationResult:\n./docs/CI.md:43:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:15:- `JAVA_HOME` should be set to JDK 21 or later. GraalVM is recommended to match CI.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:134:./gradlew javaTest -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:135:./gradlew nativeTestCompile -Pcoordinates=[group:artifact:version|k/n|all]\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:206:These tasks use Native Image runtime metadata tracing. They require a GraalVM build that supports `-H:+MetadataTracingSupport`, `-XX:TraceMetadata`, and `-XX:TraceMetadataConditionPackages`.\n./forge/tests/test_make_pr_not_for_native_image.py:14:class MakePrNotForNativeImageTests(unittest.TestCase):\n./tests/src/io.r2dbc/r2dbc-spi/1.0.0.RELEASE/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-vintage.xml:12:<property name=\"java.runtime.name\" value=\"GraalVM Runtime Environment\"/>\n./tests/src/io.r2dbc/r2dbc-spi/1.0.0.RELEASE/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-vintage.xml:19:<property name=\"java.vendor.version\" value=\"Oracle GraalVM 25.0.3+9.1\"/>\n./tests/src/io.r2dbc/r2dbc-spi/1.0.0.RELEASE/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml:12:<property name=\"java.runtime.name\" value=\"GraalVM Runtime Environment\"/>\n./tests/src/io.r2dbc/r2dbc-spi/1.0.0.RELEASE/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml:19:<property name=\"java.vendor.version\" value=\"Oracle GraalVM 25.0.3+9.1\"/>\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:90:            return \"agent: runtime test failed before nativeTest; sending failure output back to agent\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:91:        return \"agent: test failed before nativeTest; sending failure output back to agent\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:132:            if failed_task in {\"nativeTest\", None}:\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:133:                if failed_task == \"nativeTest\":\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:134:                    self._print_detail(\"result: reached nativeTest\", indent_level=2)\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/java_fix_iterative_strategy.py:158:        \"\"\"Terminal gate: verify nativeTest passes; FAILED aborts the workflow.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:252:        # Full CI-matrix GraalVM coverage, including GRAALVM_HOME_25_0, runs in\n./forge/tests/test_local_ci_verification.py:192:            command = [\"python3\", \"-c\", \"print('FAILED[javaTest][1.0.0][./gradlew test]')\"]\n./forge/tests/test_local_ci_verification.py:207:            self.assertIn(\"FAILED[javaTest]\", result.commands[0].output_excerpt)\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/optimistic_dynamic_access_strategy.py:115:                if failed_task in {\"nativeTest\", None}:\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777807979699}}
