namic access and potential issues**\\n\\nI need to consider whether using `ResolverConfig.class.getDeclaredMethod` for direct reflection in tests may lead to dynamic access, especially with user-code-filtering that includes org.xbill. The report seems to capture only library classes, but I might include new dynamic accesses. There could be issues like missing native metadata if I'm not careful. Also, using `AssertJ Arrays.stream(config.searchPath())` can help avoid NPE if searchPath is null. Another thing to note is that Java text blocks might strip leading indentation and could cause parsing issues.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering ResourceBundle fallback behavior**\\n\\nI'm looking into the Java ResourceBundle.Control fallback locale. The method getFallbackLocale returns the default locale when the target locale isn’t the default. For a Locale with empty parameters, it might revert to Locale.US, which suggests it could end up picking en_US again instead of the base. The ResourceBundle algorithm indicates that the candidate locales start with [root], and if no bundle is found, it defaults back to Locale.getDefault. However, if base is found, it shouldn't need to fallback, but en_US might still be cached from a previous request.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Y1C2zhA1MPipAUU6urrHAA1m|fc_0daabe48e56945910169f73322a0b481a2ae40dc1d61ebd1e6", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/build.gradle"}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IKJA9L7aXca8ljL2C6A3EH1L|fc_0daabe48e56945910169f73322a0cc81a2aa46820724211bf0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/dnsjava/dnsjava/2.1.7/src/test/java/dnsjava/dnsjava/ResolverConfigTest.java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 682, "output": 970, "cacheRead": 56832, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 58484, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "time